<paragraph blockId="89.[151,1437,1086,2011]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1266,1291]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Leaf mine.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[365,473,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 208–216" captionStartId="123.[151,264,1660,1683]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,193,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@123.[151,1437,193,1639]" captionTargetPageId="123" captionText="FIGURES 208–216. leaf mines; 208: Phytomyza syngenesiae (Hardy) in Tanacetum parthenium; 209: P. tarnwoodensis spec. nov. in Diervilla lonicera; 210: P. thalictrivora Spencer in Thalictrum pubescens; 211: P. tigris spec. nov. in Tiarella cordifolia; 212: P. triangularidis spec. nov. in Senecio triangularis; 213: same; 214: P. vancouveriella spec. nov. in Ƒancouveria hexandra; 215: P. verbenae spec. nov. in Ƒerbena lasiostachys; 216: P. ziziae spec. nov. in Zizia aurea (dark brown puparium on leaf surface, near margin)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1452963/files/figure.png" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Fig. 215</figureCitation>
) Linear, yellowish-green to whitish, on the upper surface, sometimes partly interparenchymal; typically following up and down most of the length of the midrib, in addition to meandering elsewhere in the leaf. The dark green to black frass is in discrete grains along the sides.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
